          <msContents>
            <summary>Copies of records of 65 autos-da-fé occurring between the years 1484 and 1502, possibly in Zaragoza (Spain), in which 605 individuals were convicted. This account includes the date of each auto-da-fé as well as the names of every individual convicted. In most cases other details, such as the accusations and punishments are present. In the majority of these cases the accusation is practicing Judaism and the punishments range from a non-specific penance to being burnt alive.</summary>
            <textLang>Spanish</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Memoria de diversos autos</title>
              <respStmt>
                <resp>former owner</resp>
                <persName>Lea, Henry Charles, 1825-1909</persName>
              </respStmt>
            </msItem>
          </msContents>
